<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@marketing_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>
<body>
  <div id="about" metal:fill-slot="contents">
    <div id="primary">
      <h2>Blueprints</h2>
      <h3 class="byline">Overview</h3>
    </div>

    <h2 class="headline">Collaborative feature development</h2>

    <table id="features">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <th>Discuss and implement ideas</th>
          <th>Manage releases</th>
          <th>Schedule meetings and sprints</th>
          <th>Create a roadmap</th>
        </tr>
        <tr class="screenshots">
          <td><img src="/+icing/blueprints-feature-discuss.png"
                   alt="Blueprints discuss ideas mini screenshot" /></td>
          <td><img src="/+icing/blueprints-feature-release.png"
                   alt="Blueprints release mini screenshot" /></td>
          <td><img src="/+icing/blueprints-feature-sprints.png"
                   alt="Blueprints sprints mini screenshot" /></td>
          <td><img src="/+icing/blueprints-feature-roadmap.png"
                   alt="Blueprints roadmap mini screenshot" /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Blueprints help your community track ideas and manage their
              implementation.
          </td>
          <td>Target blueprints to future releases of your software.</td>
          <td>Organise real world meetings, and register attendees, with an
            agenda made up of blueprints.
          </td>
          <td>Launchpad generates your project roadmap based on blueprint
            dependencies and priorities.
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div id="content">
      <div class="intro">
        <h3>About the Blueprint Tracker</h3>

        <p>Code isn't the only part of your project that can benefit from open
           development. Launchpad's unique Blueprint Tracker lets anyone
           suggest and discuss ideas for your project.
        </p>

        <p>You can accept or reject blueprints, prioritise and assign their
           development to particular team members, schedule development at
           sprints and tie them to specific releases. The Blueprint Tracker
           reduces the barriers to participating in your project and gives you
           a simple way to track new features from idea to release.
         </p>
      </div>
    </div> <!-- content -->
  </div>
</body>
</html>
